The family will have a celebration of life for those who knew and worked with Janet. The plan at this time is for April 1st. More information will become available once things are planned.

Letter from the Family:

The union meant a lot to my grandpa and he was proud to be a member of local 290. Whether it was the union Christmas party or the picnic he always tried to make it a priority. He always told lots of stories about his students when he was teaching and fondly called his students his pups. If you could tell them how proud of them he was it would be greatly appreciated. He wasnt ever a man of many words, unless he was telling a story or bragging about his union pups. Hed get the biggest grin or a mischievous look in his eye depending on the story about his union buddies . Anyway I just wanted someone, actually everyone to know how much being apart of the Pipefitters union meant to my grandpa and how thankful I am that he had your support.

Sincerely,

Ally Rovelli Granddaughter of Mike Moore
